==English==
===Noun===
'''[[lesser]] [[included]] [[offense]]''' (''plural'': '''lesser included offenses''')
# {{law}}: a [[crime]] the [[element]]s of which coincide with the elements of a more serious crime, from which the [[prosecutor]] is therefore [[preclude]]d from separately [[charging]] a [[criminal]] [[defendant]]
#:Example: A [[robbery]] is an [[assault]] combined with a [[theft]]; a person can not be criminally charged with both the robbery and the assault that occured during the robbery.